Show all your network interface
--> netstat -ie
This similar if you run --> ip a

displaying my routing table
--> netstat -r

display all current connection 
--> netstat -a

list all the current active tcp connection
--> netstat -at

print listening connection in tcp
--> netstat -lt

netstat tutorial with samples
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/unix_commands/netstat.htm

Grep the port 22 for ssh
--> netstat -an | grep :22
You can use ss command also for this
--> sudo ss -tulpn
also you can use the lsof command
--> lsof -i | grep 22

